# Project Overview

This is a Flask-based web application for managing and analyzing player data. The project follows a modular structure with clear separation of concerns.

## Main Components

- [run.py](mdc:run.py): The application entry point that initializes the Flask app and database
- [config.py](mdc:config.py): Configuration settings including database URI and environment variables
- [app/](mdc:app): Main application package containing all core functionality
  - [__init__.py](mdc:app/__init__.py): Application factory and initialization
  - [routes.py](mdc:app/routes.py): API endpoints and route handlers
  - [models/](mdc:app/models): Database models and schemas
  - [templates/](mdc:app/templates): HTML templates
  - [static/](mdc:app/static): Static assets (CSS, JS, images)
  - [utils/](mdc:app/utils): Utility functions and helpers

## Frontend
The frontend is located in the [frontend/](mdc:frontend) directory and contains the web interface components.

## Deployment
- [render.yaml](mdc:render.yaml): Render deployment configuration
- [Procfile](mdc:Procfile): Process file for deployment
- [runtime.txt](mdc:runtime.txt): Python runtime specification
- [requirements.txt](mdc:requirements.txt): Python package dependencies

